        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 26 at 4:48PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Applegate Lake, or 17 miles northeast of Happy Camp. This storm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Winds around 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern
Siskiyou County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
